            <div type="general">
               <head>General</head>
               <p xml:space="preserve">About 13 km north of the town of Bū Sǟlim in the Jandūba Gouvernorate, Balṭa is a small town surrounded by rural neighbourhoods in the mountains and flat terrain. Near the Ǧbal Bū Saʕīd, there is the tomb of the saint Sīdi Ṣālaḥ il-Balṭi on an elevation of 602 metres. Every year in August, there is a big festival in honour of the saint that brings together folkloric shows, popular arts and local heritage, as well as an exhibition of old manuscripts, competitions and the performance of traditional songs - culminating in the visit of the saints tomb, <hi rendition="#i">ḏikr</hi> and praising ceremonies.</p>
